  "prompt": "How much does it cost to buy a flight simulator?",
  "response": "The cost of a flight simulator can vary widely depending on the type and complexity. For personal use, software-based flight simulators like Microsoft Flight Simulator could range from $60 to $120 for the base game, with additional costs for premium editions, downloadable content, and peripheral hardware like high-quality joysticks, throttle controls, and VR headsets.\n\nProfessional-grade flight simulators, used for training by airlines and flight schools, can be significantly more expensive. These full-motion simulators can cost millions of dollars. For example, a full-motion Level D flight simulator could cost anywhere from $5 million to $15 million, depending on the aircraft model and the specific features included.\n\nUltimately, the cost will depend on your intended use and the level of realism and functionality you require.",
